{"type":"message","id":"d9615769","parentId":"993e0ac6","timestamp":"2026-03-22T20:40:59.344Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the config structure. I need to:\n\n1. Create a workspace directory for \"狗仔\" agent\n2. Create agent config files (SOUL.md, AGENTS.md)\n3. Create the crawler scripts for financial news\n4. Add a new agent entry to openclaw.json\n5. Add binding to route messages to the new agent\n\nHowever, since this is a Miaoda-hosted environment and the gateway is managed externally, I probably can't directly create agents in the config. Instead, I should create a sub-agent (isolated session) that runs as \"狗仔\".\n\nActually, looking at the config more carefully - I see this is running in a managed environment (miaoda). The agents.list isn't even defined, meaning it uses the default single agent setup. \n\n\nGiven the Miaoda platform constraints, creating a fully separate agent might not be feasible here. I should clarify with the user what's actually possible in this hosted environment, or suggest using a persistent sub-agent session instead, which is what the sessions_spawn function with mode=\"session\" would create.\n\nI'll build out the crawler framework and skill for financial news instead, then instantiate it as a named sub-agent that can run persistently. This gives us the compartmentalization we need without requiring gateway-level reconfiguration.","thinkingSignature":"44f9278771e1c3bbc837bb4a6f4871500f254f80e0246f4aa52e42cfa7e09463"},{"type":"text","text":"明白，我来建。先搭框架，再配 agent。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_asz6rhnwzn6t_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mkdir -p /home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/gouzai/skills\nmkdir -p /home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/gouzai/scripts\necho \"目录创建完成\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":39579,"output":335,"cacheRead":29881,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69795,"cost":{"input":0,"o