{"type":"message","id":"b74ccf62","parentId":"a2e71624","timestamp":"2026-03-22T23:54:51.522Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_qmquqvt827kn_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/extensions/openclaw-weixin/node_modules/qrcode-terminal/example/basic.png\n---\n---\n-rw-r--r-- 1 gem gem 11042 Mar 23 07:42 /tmp/jiti/auth-login-qr.0896fe0d.cjs"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":898,"aggregated":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/extensions/openclaw-weixin/node_modules/qrcode-terminal/example/basic.png\n---\n---\n-rw-r--r-- 1 gem gem 11042 Mar 23 07:42 /tmp/jiti/auth-login-qr.0896fe0d.cjs","cwd":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774223691491}}
{"type":"message","id":"7c8a1bba","parentId":"b74ccf62","timestamp":"2026-03-22T23:54:58.388Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The QR code is in the `/tmp/jiti/auth-login-qr.0896fe0d.cjs` file, which is a JavaScript file, not an image. The wechat plugin seems to be using `qrcode-terminal` to display the QR code in the terminal.\n\nLet me look at how the wechat plugin generates the QR code and if there's a way to get it as an image file. The plugin likely uses the `qrcode-terminal` package to render the QR code in the terminal. There's also a `basic.png` in the node_modules but that's just an example.\n\nActually, looking at the install process more carefully - the QR code is rendered using `qrcode-terminal` which outputs ASCII art to the terminal. \n\nThe wechat plugin connects via WebSocket to the Tencent WeChat server, and the QR code itself is generated as ASCII art rather than an image file. The most practical approach would be to either have the user run the install command themselves with terminal access, or check if there's a way to capture or redirect the QR code output to a file. Let me look at what the wechat plugin's README says about QR code handling.","thinkingSignature":"233a3f0f799d008529995683ae2a9a178a7aea6f7f106fc65e6e1f5afd86bf25"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ovot297r48ow_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /home/gem/workspace/agent/extensions/openclaw-weixin/README.zh_CN.md 2>/dev/null | head -80"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":64119,"output":292,"cacheRead":29886,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":94297,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774223691519}}
{"type":"message","id":"87a61487","parentId":"7c8a1bba","timestamp":"2026-03-22T23:54:58.422Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ovot297r48ow_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 微信\n\n[English](./README.md)\n\nOpenClaw 的微信渠道插件，支持通过扫码完成登录授权。\n\n## 前提条件\n\n已安装 [OpenClaw](https://docs.openclaw.ai/install)（需要 `openclaw` CLI 可用）。\n\n## 一键安装\n\n```bash\nnpx -y @tencent-weixin/openclaw-weixin-cli install\n```\n\n## 手动安装\n\n如果一键安装不适用，可以按以下步骤手动操作：\n\n### 1. 安装插件\n\n```bash\nopenclaw plugins install \"@tencent-weixin/openclaw-weixin\"\n```\n\n### 2. 启用插件\n\n```bash\nopenclaw config set plugins.entries.openclaw-weixin.enabled true\n```\n\n### 3. 扫码登录\n\n```bash\nopenclaw channels login --channel openclaw-weixin\n```\n\n终端会显示一个二维码，用手机扫码并在手机上确认授权。确认后，登录凭证会自动保存到本地，无需额外操作。\n\n### 4. 重启 gateway\n\n```bash\nopenclaw gateway restart\n```\n\n## 添加更多微信账号\n\n```bash\nopenclaw channels login --channel openclaw-weixin\n```\n\n每次扫码登录都会创建一个新的账号条目，支持多个微信号同时在线。\n\n## 多账号上下文隔离\n\n默认情况下，所有渠道的 AI 会话共享同一个上下文。如果希望每个微信账号的对话上下文相互隔离：\n\n```bash\nopenclaw config set agents.mode per-channel-per-peer\n```\n\n这样每个「微信账号 + 发消息用户」组合都会拥有独立的 AI 记忆，账号之间不会串台。\n\n## 后端 API 协议\n\n本插件通过 HTTP JSON API 与后端网关通信。二次开发者若需对接自有后端，需实现以下接口。\n\n所有接口均为 `POST`，请求和响应均为 JSON。通用请求头：\n\n| Header | 说明 |\n|--------|------|\n| `Content-Type` | `application/json` |\n| `AuthorizationType` | 固定值 `ilink_bot_token` |\n| `Authorization` | `Bearer <token>`（登录后获取） |\n| `X-WECHAT-UIN` | 随机 uint32 的 base64 编码 |\n\n### 接口列表\n\n| 接口 | 路径 | 说明 |"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":11,"aggregated":"# 微信\n\n[English](./README.md)\n\nOpenClaw 的微信渠道插件，支持通过扫码完成登录授权。\n\n## 前提条件\n\n已安装 [OpenClaw](https://docs.openclaw.ai/install)（需要 `openclaw` CLI 可用）。\n\n## 一键安装\n\n```bash\nnpx -y @tencent-weixin/openclaw-weixin-cli install\n```\n\n## 手动安装\n\n如果一键安装不适用，可以按以下步骤手动操作：\n\n### 1. 安装插件\n\n```bash\nopenclaw plugins install \"@tencent-weixin/openclaw-weixin\"\n```\n\n### 2. 启用插件\n\n```bash\nopenclaw config set plugins.entries.openclaw-weixin.enabled true\n```\n\n### 3. 扫码登录\n\n```bash\nopenclaw channels login --channel openclaw-weixin\n```\n\n终端会显示一个二维码，用手机扫码并在手机上确认授权。确认后，登录凭证会自动保存到本地，无需额外操作。\n\n### 4. 重启 gateway\n\n```bash\nopenclaw gateway restart\n```\n\n## 添加更多微信账号\n\n```bash\nopenclaw channels login --channel openclaw-weixin\n```\n\n每次扫码登录都会创建一个新的账号条目，支持多个微信号同时在线。\n\n## 多账号上下文隔离\n\n默认情况下，所有渠道的 AI 会话共享同一个上下文。如果希望每个微信账号的对话上下文相互隔离：\n\n```bash\nopenclaw config set agents.mode per-channel-per-peer\n```\n\n这样每个「微信账号 + 发消息用户」组合都会拥有独立的 AI 记忆，账号之间不会串台。\n\n## 后端 API 协议\n\n本插件通过 HTTP JSON API 与后端网关通信。二次开发者若需对接自有后端，需实现以下接口。\n\n所有接口均为 `POST`，请求和响应均为 JSON。通用请求头：\n\n| Header | 说明 |\n|--------|------|\n| `Content-Type` | `application/json` |\n| `AuthorizationType` | 固定值 `ilink_bot_token` |\n| `Authorization` | `Bearer <token>`（登录后获取） |\n| `X-WECHAT-UIN` | 随机 uint32 的 base64 编码 |\n\n### 接口列表\n\n| 接口 | 路径 | 说明 |","cwd":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774223698407}}
{"type":"message","id":"abeea7c1","parentId":"87a61487","timestamp":"2026-03-22T23:55:19.433Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The README says to use `openclaw channels login --channel openclaw-weixin` to scan the QR code. Let me try that - maybe it saves the QR code as an image or has a different way to display it. Actually, the `install` command already showed the QR code. The problem is that the QR code is displayed in ASCII art format, which can't be scanned from the terminal.\n\nLet me try running the login command separately, which might generate a proper QR code image file.\n\nActually, looking at the README again - it seems like the QR code is displayed in the terminal using qrcode-terminal (ASCII art). This can't be scanned directly. The user would need to either:\n1. Run the command on their own computer (where they can see the terminal)\n\n\n2. Have some way to capture the QR code as an image\n\nThe key issue is that the install command is running in the exec session (which has the ASCII QR code), and the user can't scan it from their phone. Since this is a remote server, there's no display attached to the terminal where the QR code is being rendered. The wechat plugin likely requires an attached terminal with a proper display to show the QR code in a scannable format. to generate a proper image file instead of ASCII art? Or we need to run this command locally on the user's machine. The plugin is installed on the remote Miaoda server, not the user's local computer, so the user can't scan a QR code displayed on a remote terminal.\n\nI'm considering whether we could pipe the QR code output to a file or image generator, or use the wechat plugin's screenshot functionality, but these are all getting complicated. The real issue is that the plugin displays an ASCII QR code that the user can't scan remotely. They either need to run the command locally, or I need to figure out how to generate a proper image file they can access.\n\nLooking at the plugin architecture, it seems to use a backend service to relay messages, which means the QR code is tied to that relay service. I could try checking if the wechat CLI has a flag to output the QR code as a file, or explore the qrcode-terminal package to see if there's a way to generate an actual image instead of ASCII art. Alternatively, I could write a Python script to render the QR code data to an image file using a library like reportlab, but I'd need to extract the QR data first.\n\nActually, I realize the install command is still running and waiting for the scan. If I let it run indefinitely, the user could try scanning from their phone, but the ASCII QR code displayed in the terminal can't be scanned by a phone camera. The better approach would be to use the wechat plugin's screenshot functionality to capture the QR code from the terminal and send it to the user, or try using Python to generate a proper QR code image from the ASCII representation.\n\nSince the plugin is running in this exec session and I can take screenshots, I could try capturing the terminal output with the ASCII QR code, but that's impractical. A simpler solution would be to kill the current waiting session, generate the QR code as an actual image file using a QR code library, and then let the user scan that image instead.\n\nLooking at the wechat plugin's actual files, it uses `qrcode-terminal` to render the QR code as ASCII art in the terminal, so there's no image file generated automatically. I could either write a Python script to generate a proper QR code image from the plugin's output, or just have the user run the login command locally on their own machine where they can see the terminal directly.\n\nSince the gateway is already running, I should check if the wechat plugin has already established a connection or if there's a saved session. Let me query the gateway status to see if it's already authenticated with WeChat.","thinkingSignature":"f53399b7bb27e6c7d727a442ba2cf61909d03427847891d623fd62f50d71017a"},{"type":"text","text":"QR码是 ASCII 艺术图案，手机扫不了。需要生成图片格式的二维码。看看能不能从插件里提取数据：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cn3orj22lym0_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /home/gem/workspace/agent/extensions/openclaw-weixin/src/messaging/process-message.ts 2>/dev/null | head -50\necho \"---\"\n# 看wechat插件有没有生成QR图片的方法\ngrep -r \"qr\\|QR\\|qrcode\" /home/gem/workspace/agent/extensions/openclaw-weixin/src/ 2>/dev/null | grep -v node_modules | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":64872,"output":916,"cacheRead":29886,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":95674,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774223698420}}
