{"type":"message","id":"6c6fb303","parentId":"f2a4fd73","timestamp":"2026-03-22T23:56:11.995Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_i5r2h82b5ut0_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"CHANGELOG.md\nCHANGELOG.zh_CN.md\nindex.ts\nLICENSE\nnode_modules\nopenclaw.plugin.json\npackage.json\npackage-lock.json\nREADME.md\nREADME.zh_CN.md\nsrc\n---\n/home/gem/.cache/ms-playwright/chromium-1208/chrome-linux64/product_logo_48.png\n/home/gem/.local/lib/python3.12/site-packages/playwright/driver/package/lib/server/chromium/appIcon.png\n---\nOpenClaw 的微信渠道插件，支持通过扫码完成登录授权。\n\n## 前提条件\n\n已安装 [OpenClaw](https://docs.openclaw.ai/install)（需要 `openclaw` CLI 可用）。\n\n--\n### 3. 扫码登录\n\n```bash\nopenclaw channels login --channel openclaw-weixin\n```\n\n终端会显示一个二维码，用手机扫码并在手机上确认授权。确认后，登录凭证会自动保存到本地，无需额外操作。\n\n### 4. 重启 gateway\n\n```bash\nopenclaw gateway restart\n--\n每次扫码登录都会创建一个新的账号条目，支持多个微信号同时在线。\n\n## 多账号上下文隔离\n\n默认情况下，所有渠道的 AI 会话共享同一个上下文。如果希望每个微信账号的对话上下文相互隔离："}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":310,"aggregated":"CHANGELOG.md\nCHANGELOG.zh_CN.md\nindex.ts\nLICENSE\nnode_modules\nopenclaw.plugin.json\npackage.json\npackage-lock.json\nREADME.md\nREADME.zh_CN.md\nsrc\n---\n/home/gem/.cache/ms-playwright/chromium-1208/chrome-linux64/product_logo_48.png\n/home/gem/.local/lib/python3.12/site-packages/playwright/driver/package/lib/server/chromium/appIcon.png\n---\nOpenClaw 的微信渠道插件，支持通过扫码完成登录授权。\n\n## 前提条件\n\n已安装 [OpenClaw](https://docs.openclaw.ai/install)（需要 `openclaw` CLI 可用）。\n\n--\n### 3. 扫码登录\n\n```bash\nopenclaw channels login --channel openclaw-weixin\n```\n\n终端会显示一个二维码，用手机扫码并在手机上确认授权。确认后，登录凭证会自动保存到本地，无需额外操作。\n\n### 4. 重启 gateway\n\n```bash\nopenclaw gateway restart\n--\n每次扫码登录都会创建一个新的账号条目，支持多个微信号同时在线。\n\n## 多账号上下文隔离\n\n默认情况下，所有渠道的 AI 会话共享同一个上下文。如果希望每个微信账号的对话上下文相互隔离：","cwd":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774223771983}}
{"type":"message","id":"6dc5e8b2","parentId":"6c6fb303","timestamp":"2026-03-22T23:56:23.877Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The problem is clear: the QR code is displayed in ASCII art in the terminal, but the user needs to scan it with their phone. The WeChat plugin uses `qrcode-terminal` which renders QR in ASCII, not as an image file.\n\nThere might be a way to get the actual QR code image. Let me check the source code of the plugin to see if there's a way to get the QR code data (not the rendered ASCII), which I could then use to generate an image.\n\nActually, looking at the plugin's source - it uses `@open-ability/qrcode-terminal` which has a `getQRCode` or similar method that returns the raw QR data (not rendered). I could potentially:\n\n\n- Intercept the raw QR data before it's rendered to ASCII\n- Generate a proper PNG image from that data using Python's qrcode library\n- Send the image to the user via Feishu so they can scan it\n\nBut wait, the session timed out anyway. Let me try running the login command directly with PTY to see if it outputs the QR code data that I could use. Actually, the most straightforward approach is to use Python to generate a QR code image directly from the plugin's data source.\n\nLet me check if there's a way to get the raw QR data from the plugin, then I can generate a proper image file and send it via Feishu. Looking at the `process-message.ts` warning, it seems like the plugin connects to an external backend. The QR code is probably fetched from there. The `npx` command just downloads and runs the plugin, but the actual QR code is generated by the plugin itself, so I need to figure out how to extract that data before it gets rendered to ASCII. The real issue is that a text-based terminal can't display scannable QR codes. Maybe I should try running the login command with PTY to see if it can render an image format instead, or check if the plugin exposes a file-based QR code I can work with.","thinkingSignature":"2f50df9d615cccbd6e0ebc1d9741f23a479f181e29843308be22fb557922409f"},{"type":"text","text":"QR码是ASCII艺术文本，手机扫不了。需要找其他方式。看看能不能直接生成图片版：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zjkzthggusfd_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"pip show qrcode 2>/dev/null | head -3\necho \"---\"\npython3 -c \"import qrcode; print('qrcode available')\" 2>/dev/null || echo \"qrcode not installed\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":65044,"output":501,"cacheRead":29886,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":95431,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774223771994}}
