{"type":"message","id":"86637d6d","parentId":"277337bf","timestamp":"2026-03-22T23:57:28.368Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The API returned a URL as the `qrcode_img_content`, not a base64 image! It's a URL to the liteapp: `https://liteapp.weixin.qq.com/q/7GiQu1?qrcode=...`\n\nThis means the QR code is displayed in the WeChat app by visiting this URL, not as a direct image. So the user needs to either:1. Open this URL in WeChat to see the QR code2. Or the plugin uses some other mechanism to display the QR in the terminal\n\nBut actually, the `qrcode` field is a short token. The URL `https://liteapp.weixin.qq.com/q/7GiQu1?qrcode=...` is probably the QR code content URL that WeChat's liteapp loads.\n\n\nSince this URL scheme only works within WeChat itself, I can't generate a scannable QR code from here without the actual QR code image data. I need to either find if there's another API endpoint that returns the image directly, or reconsider this approach entirely.\n\nThe `npx` command was interactive and timed out, so let me try using `openclaw channels login` directly and piping its output to a file so I can capture the QR code before it expires.","thinkingSignature":"e92b7ca0a429b222c3143cc625fe2e963fc162743b7ab6edaf05478862126803"},{"type":"text","text":"API返回的是一个URL，不是图片。需要用正确的方式生成二维码图片：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_yklr6lls5jlx_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'EOF'\nimport qrcode\nimport sys\n\n# 这个URL就是二维码的内容\nurl = \"https://liteapp.weixin.qq.com/q/7GiQu1?qrcode=17f665c862b24b29fbac5c3868f1c094&bot_type=3\"\n\nimg = qrcode.make(url)\nimg.save(\"/tmp/weixin_qr.png\")\nprint(\"QR图片已保存到 /tmp/weixin_qr.png\")\nprint(f\"图片大小: {img.pixel_size if hasattr(img, 'pixel_size') else 'unknown'}\")\nEOF"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":70551,"output":419,"cacheRead":29886,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":100856,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cach