{"type":"message","id":"a7c5dbc2","parentId":"e2a73a0f","timestamp":"2026-03-23T00:14:01.977Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see two important things:\n1. **Duplicate plugin warning**: `plugins.entries.openclaw-weixin: plugin openclaw-weixin: duplicate plugin id detected; later plugin may be overridden` - this suggests the weixin plugin is being loaded twice, once from the npm package and once from somewhere else.\n\n2. The weixin channel is in the config (`channels.openclaw-weixin`) but I don't see it initializing in the gateway logs after the restart.\n\nLet me check the config for duplicate plugin entries.","thinkingSignature":"7ded28d676f5ba35de6a55d888dc78e602ebf6d5123cf90741cb24c6d41d1b06"},{"type":"text","text":"看到问题了！**微信插件重复加载**导致冲突：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4580px4fjxus_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /home/gem/workspace/agent/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json\nd = json.load(sys.stdin)\nplugins = d.get('plugins', {})\nprint('allow:', plugins.get('allow', []))\nentries = plugins.get('entries', {})\nprint('entries:')\nfor k, v in entries.items():\n    print(f'  {k}: {v}')\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":91078,"output":221,"cacheRead":29886,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":121185,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774224834420}}
