{"type":"message","id":"e337a102","parentId":"350a7e96","timestamp":"2026-03-23T00:14:10.896Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The config looks fine. The issue is that there are TWO instances of the openclaw-weixin plugin being loaded. The error log said:\n\n```\nConfig warnings:\n- plugins.entries.openclaw-weixin: plugin openclaw-weixin: duplicate plugin id detected; later plugin may be overridden\n```\n\nThis means the plugin is installed in two places (maybe once in node_modules and once in the extensions folder). This is causing the duplicate warning.\n\nActually, looking at the `plugins.allow` list: `['openclaw-lark', 'feishu-greeting', 'miaoda-keepalive', 'openclaw-weixin']` - the openclaw-weixin is there. \n\nThe real problem might be that `openclaw-weixin` is installed both as a local plugin in the extensions directory and as a npm package in node_modules, so when the plugin loader finds both copies it registers the same ID twice and the second one gets ignored.","thinkingSignature":"ce849d2a7cf8dd527af76e2d5feba7ba48a877928b1a092ba8cd5309a98d4757"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_09j46pxgivie_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find /home/gem/workspace/agent -name \"openclaw-weixin\" -not -path \"*/node_modules/*\" -not -path \"*/.git/*\" 2>/dev/null\necho \"---\"\nfind /home/gem/workspace/agent -name \"package.json\" -path \"*/openclaw-weixin/*\" -not -path \"*/node_modules/*\" 2>/dev/null | xargs cat 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print('name:', d.get('name')); print('version:', d.get('version'))\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":91470,"output":353,"cacheRead":29886,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":121709,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774224842032}}
