{"type":"message","id":"6a6d1b5e","parentId":"ab287f4f","timestamp":"2026-03-23T00:14:49.435Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is clear now - there's a \"duplicate plugin id detected\" warning, which means the weixin plugin is registered twice and the second one overrides the first (or fails). But looking at the 08:11 startup, the weixin plugin doesn't show up at all.\n\nWait, but the error says \"later plugin may be overridden\" - so the plugin IS being found, just potentially overridden. But I don't see it in the startup log at 08:11.\n\nActually, I think the issue might be that the weixin plugin failed to load due to some error. Let me check if there's something in the log about plugin loading failures.\n\nActually, looking more carefully - the weixin plugin IS in the config at `channels.openclaw-weixin`. But the config `plugins.entries` also has `openclaw-weixin`. \n\nI think the weixin plugin has both a `channels` entry and a `plugins` entry, and it's being loaded twice which causes the duplicate warning. The real problem is that when the gateway started at 08:11, the weixin plugin wasn't registered at all, even though it's in the config. So the duplicate warning from 07:54 happened during an earlier startup attempt, but by 08:11 the plugin wasn't even showing up.\n\nLooking back at the install output from 07:54, it mentioned \"Already at version 1.0.2\" and the config already had the plugin listed. The real issue might be that when I tried to set the channel config at 08:04, something went wrong with the gateway restart that prevented the plugin from loading properly on the next startup.\n\nThe gateway restarted at 08:10 with the SIGTERM and started fresh at 08:11, but the weixin plugin never showed up in the logs. I'm wondering if there's a configuration problem with how the channel and plugin entries are set up - specifically whether the `channels.openclaw-weixin` and `plugins.entries.openclaw-weixin` configurations are conflicting or if one of them is malformed in a way that's preventing the plugin from initializing. The duplicate warning suggests the plugin is being registered twice, but the second registration overwrites the first. However, I'm not seeing the weixin plugin appear at all in the 08:11 startup, even though the config warnings from 07:54 indicate it was loaded then. This could mean the plugin failed to initialize properly or there's a timing issue with how it's being loaded during startup.","thinkingSignature":"83a8f4385b1313689a3dc2e46ba76aa46a888d0562da72e20223da5d3e4d8900"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5oh2wo3s40gc_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -E \"openclaw-weixin|weixin.*start|weixin.*channel|weixin.*register|channel.*start|weixin.*init\" /var/log/openclaw/info.log 2>/dev/null | grep -v \"tool call\\|tool done\" | tail -10\necho \"===\"\n# Check if the weixin plugin has any tools that should show up\ngrep \"Registered.*weixin\\|weixin.*Registered\\|im.weixin\" /var/log/openclaw/info.log 2>/dev/null | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":96921,"output":638,"cacheRead":29886,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":127445,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774224874566}}
